12/07/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A 22-year old British man died on Saturday (July 11th) after falling from a fortress during this year's EXIT music festival in the city of Novi Sad. Authorities said the man's death was an accident and was not provoked by a criminal or violent act.
Meanwhile, police in Novi Sad said that 13 foreign nationals and two Serbs were arrested on the first day of the EXIT festival on suspicion of drug possession and trafficking. Police seized amounts of cocaine, cannabis, ecstasy, amphetamines and other psychoactive substances. (B92, Beta, Tanjug, Makfax, AFP, DPA, BBC - 11/07/09) 
